Class Attribute

  • java.lang.Object
    • life.genny.qwandaq.CoreEntity
      • life.genny.qwandaq.CodedEntity
        • life.genny.qwandaq.attribute.Attribute
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CoreEntityInterface, Serializable, Comparable<Object>, CreatedIntf
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AttributeBoolean, AttributeDate, AttributeDateRange, AttributeDateTime, AttributeDouble, AttributeInteger, AttributeLink, AttributeLong, AttributeMoney, AttributeText, AttributeTime
    @Entity
public class Attribute
extends CodedEntity
implements Serializable
    Attribute represents a distinct abstract Fact about a target entity managed in the Qwanda library. An attribute may be used directly in processing meaning for a target entity. Such processing may be in relation to a comparison score against another target entity, or to generate more attribute information via inference and induction This attribute information includes:
    • The Human Readable name for this attibute (used for summary lists)
    • The unique code for the attribute
    • The description of the attribute
    • The answerType that represents the format of the attribute

    Attributes represent facts about a target.
